verbose_text: In this article, we examine the effects of prior and current levels of AER on the rate of decline in estimated GFR (eGFR) and on the risk of decreased levels of eGFR (< 60 ml/min/1.73 m 2) in subjects with type 1 diabetes in the Diabetes Control and Complications Trial (DCCT) and/or the follow-up Epidemiology of Diabetes Interventions and Complications (EDIC) study.
